<image 1> What does the shaded area represent? P(___< x < ___)

A. 5,6
B. 5,7
C. 6,7
D. 6,8

To determine what the shaded area represents, we need to identify the range of \( x \) values that correspond to the shaded region.

The shaded area is between two vertical lines on the x-axis. The left boundary of the shaded area is at \( x = 6 \), and the right boundary is at \( x = 7 \).

Therefore, the shaded area represents the probability \( P(6 < x < 7) \).

The correct answer is:

C. 6,7
